dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large image database for use in visual object recognition, containing more than 14 million images, with at least one million images having bounding boxes. It has over 20,000 categories, each typically consisting of hundreds of images.
dcterms:title: ImageNet

dcterms:description: The Cats and Dogs Dataset consists of more than three million images of cats and dogs, manually classified by people, and is used for training models to distinguish between the two species.
dcterms:title: Cats and Dogs Dataset

dcterms:creator: L. Fei-Fei

dcterms:description: Caltech-101 is a database of images intended for computer vision research, containing 9,146 images across 101 distinct object categories, with annotations describing the outlines in each image.
dcterms:title: Caltech-101
